715816f-a.text:
West 215th Street, north side, east from, but not including Columbus (9th) Ave., to the Harlem River. Buildings in the foreground, are used by the Burns Bros., Coal Company.

June 8, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

710450f-a.text:
Ninth Ave., at the N.E. corner of West 216th Street, showing the former power plant, used by George Grey Barnard as a studio. Photographers vantage point is at the N.W. corner of Ninth Ave. and West 215th Street.

June 8, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.
